      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng" n="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0013.tlg018.perseus-eng2">
      <head>To Hermes</head>
      <milestone n="1" unit="card"/>
          <l n="1"><milestone unit="Para" ed="P"/>I sing of Cyllenian Hermes, the Slayer of Argus, lord of Cyllene and <placeName key="tgn,7002735">Arcadia</placeName> rich in flocks, luck-bringing messenger of the deathless gods. He was born of Maia, the daughter of Atlas, when she had mated with Zeus,â€”</l>
          <l n="5">a shy goddess she. Ever she avoided the throng of the blessed gods and lived in a shadowy cave, and there the Son of Cronos used to lie with the rich-tressed nymph at dead of night, while white-armed Hera lay bound in sweet sleep: and neither deathless god nor mortal man knew it.</l>
          <l n="10"><milestone unit="Para" ed="P"/>And so hail to you, Son of Zeus and Maia; with you I have begun: now I will turn to another song!<milestone unit="Para" ed="P"/>Hail, Hermes, giver of grace, guide, and giver of good things! </l>
      </div>
